The League Management Company (LMC), has rescheduled some of the matches involving six teams in the ongoing 2021 season due to some circumstances. According to the press release from the league organiser, the changes will involve from Match-day 8 and 9 fixtures of the league. Six teams including Nasarawa United, Katsina United, Akwa United, FC Ifeanyi Ubah, Rivers United and Heartland FC were all affected. The original date of the match 3rd and 4th of February 2021 were moved to 7th and 8th of the same month. The matches include Heartland FC v IfeanyiUbah, Rivers United v Nasarawa United and Akwa United v Katsina United.